      "code": "def f(x):\n    \"\"\"Heuristic diabetes-like classifier from tabular features.\n    Expects x as a dict (or object with same attribute names).\"\"\"\n    def get(k, default=0.0):\n        v = x.get(k, default) if isinstance(x, dict) else getattr(x, k, default)\n        try:\n            v = float(v)\n        except Exception:\n            v = float(default)\n        # treat negative placeholders as missing\n        return v if v > 0 else 0.0\n\n    preg = get('pregnancies')\n    glu  = get('plasma_glucose')\n    bp   = get('diastolic_blood_pressure')\n    tri  = get('triceps_skinfold')\n    ins  = get('serum_insulin')\n    bmi  = get('bmi')\n    ped  = get('diabetes_pedigree')\n    age  = get('age')\n\n    score = (\n        0.026 * glu +\n        0.032 * bmi +\n        1.35  * ped +\n        0.018 * age +\n        0.030 * preg +\n        0.006 * bp +\n        0.002 * tri -\n        0.0012 * ins -\n        8.3\n    )\n\n    # dampen some high-glucose / low-context patterns seen in the data\n    if glu > 210 and ped < 0.45 and bmi < 58 and age < 30:\n        score -= 1.0\n    if glu > 290 and ins > 800:\n        score -= 1.2\n\n    return 1 if score > 0 else 0\n",
